{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:59:11.530Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "After tokenization, each piece maps to an integer "}, {"type": "text", "text": "token ID", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 an index into the model vocabulary. The "}, {"type": "text", "text": "embedding layer", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " converts those IDs into dense vectors the transformer processes. This text-to-ID-to-vector pipeline is the front door of every LLM forward pass; agent developers who understand it avoid subtle bugs when counting tokens, mixing models, or inspecting internal states."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Token IDs to embedding vectors: LLM forward pass front door with matrix lookup diagram"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Token IDs are non-negative integers in "}, {"type": "text", "text": "[0, vocab_size)", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ". The tokenizer maintains bidirectional maps: string piece \u2194 ID. Special tokens (BOS, EOS, padding, chat markers) occupy reserved IDs. The embedding matrix "}, {"type": "text", "text": "E \u2208 \u211d^{vocab_size \u00d7 embed_dim}", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " stores one learnable vector per vocabulary entry; a forward pass gathers rows by ID to build the input tensor shape "}, {"type": "text", "text": "[batch, seq_len, embed_dim]", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "APIs bill and bound context by token count \u2014 IDs are what gets counted. Logit bias, constrained decoding, and token healing operate on IDs, not raw strings. When an agent swaps models, token IDs change even if the prompt text is identical. Embedding dimensions must match downstream layers; loading weights from a checkpoint with a different vocabulary size fails without resizing embeddings."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Discrete interface", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 models consume fixed-size integer sequences suitable for GPU batching"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Learned semantics", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 embeddings capture distributional meaning from pre-training"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Efficient lookup", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 embedding gather is O(seq_len) and cheap versus attention"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inspectable control", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 APIs expose IDs for bias, banning, and debugging generation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Token IDs are model-specific \u2014 not portable across tokenizers or checkpoints"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Embedding table size grows with vocabulary (see vocabulary-size topic for memory trade-offs)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rare tokens may have under-trained embeddings if they appear infrequently in pre-training"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adding new tokens after training requires resizing embeddings and usually continued training"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How it works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "From text to input_ids"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Normalize and split text with the model's tokenizer (subword merges, special token rules)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Map each token string to its vocabulary index \u2192 list of token IDs (input_ids)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optionally add attention_mask (1 for real tokens, 0 for padding) and position information"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Embedding layer indexes E[input_ids] \u2192 floating-point tensor fed to transformer blocks"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Embeddings in the forward pass"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each transformer layer updates hidden states; the initial embedding is the sum (or concatenation, in some architectures) of token embeddings and positional embeddings. The output head at the final layer projects hidden states back to "}, {"type": "text", "text": "vocab_size", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " logits \u2014 the mirror of the input embedding table \u2014 to predict the next token ID during generation."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to use it"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Counting tokens before API calls \u2014 encode to IDs and measure sequence length"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Applying logit bias or token suppression \u2014 reference IDs from the model tokenizer"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loading or fine-tuning models \u2014 verify input_ids shape and embedding weight dimensions match"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Debugging generation \u2014 map output IDs back to strings with decode()"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to implement"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Obtain token IDs and inspect the embedding layer with Hugging Face transformers:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from transformers import AutoTokenizer, AutoModelForCausalLM\nimport torch\n\nmodel_id = \"meta-llama/Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct\"\ntokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(model_id)\nmodel = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(model_id, torch_dtype=torch.float16)\n\nprompt = \"List three steps to validate a tool call schema.\"\nencoded = tokenizer(prompt, return_tensors=\"pt\")\ninput_ids = encoded[\"input_ids\"]\n\nprint(\"Token IDs:\", input_ids[0].tolist())\nprint(\"Tokens:\", tokenizer.convert_ids_to_tokens(input_ids[0]))\nprint(\"Token count:\", input_ids.shape[1])\n\nembed_layer = model.get_input_embeddings()\nprint(\"Embedding shape:\", embed_layer.weight.shape)  # [vocab_size, embed_dim]\n\nwith torch.no_grad():\n    token_vectors = embed_layer(input_ids)\nprint(\"Input tensor shape:\", token_vectors.shape)  # [1, seq_len, embed_dim]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Count tokens with tiktoken for OpenAI-compatible APIs:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import tiktoken\n\nenc = tiktoken.get_encoding(\"cl100k_base\")\ntext = \"System: You are a tool-using agent.\\nUser: Search docs for PEFT.\"\nids = enc.encode(text)\nprint(len(ids), \"tokens\")\nprint(ids[:8], \"\u2192\", [enc.decode([i]) for i in ids[:8]])"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Examples"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The string "}, {"type": "text", "text": "hello", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " might map to ID 15339 in one GPT tokenizer and a different ID in Llama's SentencePiece vocabulary. Decoding ID 15339 without the matching vocabulary produces wrong text or errors."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Real-world example"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "An agent runtime applies logit bias to encourage JSON output by boosting IDs for "}, {"type": "text", "text": "{", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "text": "}", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Engineers copy bias values from a blog post targeting GPT-3.5 token IDs; on a newer model the IDs differ and bias has no effect. Fix: call "}, {"type": "text", "text": "tokenizer.convert_tokens_to_ids([\"{\", \"}\"])", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " on the deployed model's tokenizer."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using string length or word count instead of token IDs for context budgeting"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Assuming the same integer means the same token across models or tokenizer versions"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Feeding one model's input_ids into another model's forward pass"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Forgetting special tokens in counts when add_special_tokens=True (default in many APIs)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Confusing embedding dimension (hidden size) with vocabulary size"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best practices"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Always encode with the same tokenizer bundled with the model checkpoint"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use return_tensors and attention_mask for batch-safe inference code"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Log both token strings and IDs when debugging agent prompts"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When resizing vocabulary for new special tokens, initialize new embedding rows carefully"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Performance and scalability"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Embedding lookup is memory-bandwidth bound but negligible versus attention at long contexts. The embedding matrix itself can be large for 100K+ vocabularies \u2014 quantizing or tying input/output embeddings reduces footprint. In multi-tenant agent servers, batch requests with left-padding and shared static prefix caching where the framework supports it."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Tooling and ecosystem"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "transformers AutoTokenizer", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 encode, decode, convert_ids_to_tokens"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tiktoken", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 OpenAI model token counting"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "model.get_input_embeddings()", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 access embedding weights in PyTorch models"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "API usage endpoints", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 report prompt/completion token counts as ID totals"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Security and reliability"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Token ID confusion enables prompt-injection variants that exploit special-token boundaries. Never trust client-supplied token IDs \u2014 always re-tokenize text server-side. When merging adapters or LoRA weights, verify vocabulary and embedding shapes match the base checkpoint."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Token IDs are "}, {"type": "text", "text": "row numbers in a dictionary table", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": "; embeddings are the "}, {"type": "text", "text": "content of each row", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ". The transformer never sees raw text \u2014 only the vectors looked up by those row numbers."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Tokenizers map text pieces to integer IDs; embedding layers map IDs to vectors"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "input_ids drive both token counting and the first step of model inference"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Token IDs are model-specific \u2014 always use the matching tokenizer"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Output logits mirror vocabulary size; generation predicts the next token ID"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Agent debugging and API cost estimation start with correct encode/decode of IDs"}]}]}]}]}}